        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
          "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-08-16 17:31:36.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-1755 osc: solve a race between fsync and truncate",
        "message": "LU-1755 osc: solve a race between fsync and truncate\n\nIf an OSC extent is being truncated when fsync is called, it will\nhave oe_fsync_wait set but no oe_urgent or oe_hp set. This causes\nproblem because when the extent changes OES_CACHE later, it won't\nbe written out immediately because urgent bit is not set.\n\nThis problem can be fixed by checking oe_fsync_wait bit and set urgent\nbit correspondingly when changing osc extent's state from OES_TRUNC to\nOES_CACHE at the end of truncate.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I755baac066375a92730b14de1c470c66baad5320\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
